# Session 2 — Client-Side Prediction for Smooth Movement

Date: 2026-04-01

---

## What Was Done

Implemented client-side prediction for the local player to eliminate input lag.
At 20 TPS the round-trip latency (input → server tick → state diff back) caused
visibly jerky movement. The local player now moves immediately on keypress using
the same physics the server runs; the server's authoritative position reconciles
the prediction each tick.

Remote players are unaffected — they still render from raw server state at 20fps
(interpolation is future work).

