## `LocalPlayerPredictor` (`prediction.ts`)

Mirrors the server's `movePlayer` + `collidesWithGrid` logic exactly.

### Collision

```
HALF = 0.45  (identical to server)
isSolid: WALL_HARD | WALL_SOFT | BOMB
collides: 4-corner AABB check, returns true if any corner hits a solid tile or goes out of bounds
```

BOMB tiles are always treated as solid (no own-bomb passthrough tracking).
If the player drops a bomb and immediately walks, prediction briefly shows them
blocked; the server corrects within one tick. Accepted tradeoff.

### `advance(dir, speedMult, grid, nowMs)`

Called every render frame (~60 fps). Uses real elapsed `dt` instead of the fixed
server DT so position advances smoothly.

```
delta = PLAYER_SPEED * speedMult * dt
Try newX, newY → if no collision, move
Corner-rounding (mirror of server):
  dx != 0: nudge Y toward Math.round(py), retry X+nudgedY, retry nudgedY only
  dy != 0: nudge X toward Math.round(px), retry nudgedX+Y, retry nudgedX only
Fully blocked → don't move
dt is capped at 100 ms to prevent huge jumps after tab sleep
```

### `reconcile(serverX, serverY)`

Called on every `game:tick` after `applyDiff`:

```
errSq = (px - serverX)² + (py - serverY)²
errSq > 0.09  (> 0.3 tiles) → snap immediately
errSq > 0.0001              → gentle lerp: px += (serverX - px) * 0.4
errSq ≈ 0                   → already aligned, skip
```

### `init(serverX, serverY)` / `reset()`

- `init` seeds position + `lastFrameMs` when IN_GAME starts
- `reset` deactivates predictor; `advance`/`reconcile` are no-ops when inactive

